thread.title: Some Markets Rebound, but Chinese Stocks Fall

author: Gregor Stuart Hunter
title: Some Markets Rebound, but Chinese Stocks Fall
text:
U.S. stocks slide after Wednesday’s rebound Tech and bank earnings in focus U.S. 10-year Treasury yields near highest since 2014 U.S. stocks slid Thursday, continuing this week’s whipsaw action in equities and bond markets.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 77 points, or 0.3%, to 26072 shortly after the opening bell. The S&P 500 declined 0.2% and the Nasdaq Composite lost 0.3%.
